Selenium Maven Plugin

 Provides support for using {{{http://www.openqa.org/selenium}Selenium}} with Maven 2.
 
 Use this plugin to start a Selenium {{{http://www.openqa.org/selenium-rc/}Remote Control}}
 server to support automated web-application testing.
 
 This plugin is intended to support usage of the
 {{{http://www.openqa.org/selenium-rc/java.html}Selenium Java Client Driver}}
 when running <regular Surefire tests>.  Use {{{http://www.openqa.org/selenium-ide}Selenium IDE}}
 to help generate the initial Java code for the tests, and then augment as needed.

* Goals Overview

 * {{{start-server-mojo.html}selenium:start-server}}: Start the Selenium server.
 
 * {{{stop-server-mojo.html}selenium:stop-server}}: Stop the Selenium server.
 
 * {{{selenese-mojo.html}selenium:selenese}}: Run a suite of HTML Selenese tests.
 
 * {{{xvfb-mojo.html}selenium:xvfb}}: Starts an Xvfb instance suitable for handling X11 displays for headless systems.
 
